topic.title: Anyone still unable to make ZeroIDs with Tor Browser?
topic.body: It still gives me the "try again later" error every time I try. I even tried reinstalling both ZeroNet and Tor Browser and no joy. What's up with this? Will it be fixed or will Tor exit nodes be banned forever from ZeroID?

1567454449_13VoN9gGPqenYYp56NTtHdbZuAoka.body:
> [gitcenter](#comment_942_1Cy3ntkN2GN9MH6EaW6eHpi4YoRS2nK5Di): The check order is the following: [...]

There's some weak evidence that's not the case, since I got "Network almost full" and then seconds later was able to generate an ID with no issues from a clearnet address.

> [gitcenter](#comment_949_1Cy3ntkN2GN9MH6EaW6eHpi4YoRS2nK5Di): That falls into my theory well, e.g. someone registered an account 59 minutes ago or something. But I'm pretty sure that the order is correct.

Now the message is
>Error while during request: Forbidden
>Please try again later..
Any theory as to the significance of the dots?
